Component	Description
1ï¸âƒ£ Playground (Frontend)	A simple web UI built with HTML/JS and hosted on GitHub Pages. Users enter meeting summaries or instructions.
2ï¸âƒ£ Planner Agent (Backend)	FastAPI app on Google Cloud Run. Receives meeting text, uses Gemini API to refine tasks, and creates structured JSON plans. Publishes to Pub/Sub and stores them in Firestore.
3ï¸âƒ£ Pub/Sub Topic (planner-to-executor)	Asynchronous message bus between Planner and Executor. Provides decoupled, scalable event flow.
4ï¸âƒ£ Firestore (plans collection)	Stores structured task plans with metadata (plan_id, timestamp, actions).
5ï¸âƒ£ Executor Agent	(Planned next stage) Another Cloud Run service that subscribes to Pub/Sub messages and executes tasks, e.g., sending emails or creating reports.
6ï¸âƒ£ Cloud Build & Container Registry	Handles Docker image builds and deployment automation.
7ï¸âƒ£ Gemini API	Enhances meeting text understanding and produces refined summaries or structured JSON.

